Author:
Vol / Page:  35
Edition:
Quote:  Kakariki are a native New Zealand member of the parrot family. They come in three varieties: red-crowned, the most common but confined to offshore islands; yellow crowned, which had mainland populations but were rarer; and orange-fronted, which were very rare.
